Generalize discount banners (veterans + first resp + students + teachers)

Same GovX pattern, four groups instead of one.

Server (api/config.js) now returns a discountBanners array with one
entry per configured group:
  - veteran: GOVX_VETERAN_URL (legacy: GOVX_VERIFY_URL accepted)
  - first_responder: GOVX_FIRSTRESP_URL
  - student: GOVX_STUDENT_URL
  - teacher: GOVX_TEACHER_URL

Each group has its own DISCOUNT_PERCENT env var (default 10). Groups
with no URL set are filtered out — the banner array only includes
the configured ones.

Legacy fields (veteranVerifyUrl, veteranDiscountPercent) still
returned for any in-flight cached client. Will remove later.

Cart UI now renders the array. Empty when nothing configured. One
small banner per group, stacked. URLs validated http(s)-only on the
client (defense vs malformed env). Built via DOM API for XSS safety.

USER_TODOS updated:
- Section 7c renamed and rewritten to cover all four groups
- .env.example documents all four URL/percent pairs

No new infrastructure required. Existing GovX accounts work — just
create more campaigns in their dashboard for the new groups, each
pointing at a matching Stripe promotion code.

